17:45.936 --> 17:47.103
Andy!

17:47.170 --> 17:49.205
I got two microphones,
a four-track recorder,

17:49.272 --> 17:51.741
and every bass tab
to Dave Matthews ever.

17:51.808 --> 17:52.942
- <i>Vamos!</i>
<i>- We're gonna jam</i>

17:53.009 --> 17:54.410
for, like, nine hours.
Is that cool?

17:54.478 --> 17:55.478
- Yeah.
- All right.

17:55.545 --> 17:57.646
That's ridiculous.

17:57.714 --> 17:59.482
Now, why should
the bill of rights

17:59.549 --> 18:02.151
be in the official time capsule

18:02.219 --> 18:04.487
but this painting of my dog

18:04.554 --> 18:07.056
is in time capsule seven?

18:07.124 --> 18:10.092
Well, I think pet paintings/ashes

18:10.160 --> 18:11.961
are in time capsule four.

18:12.028 --> 18:14.764
No, that's baseball cards.

18:14.831 --> 18:16.532
No, baseball cards

18:16.600 --> 18:19.268
are in time capsule nine:
Childhood memorabilia.

18:19.336 --> 18:20.503
Honestly,
<i>Twilight</i> could go

18:20.570 --> 18:22.104
in almost any of these
categories.

18:22.172 --> 18:23.873
Oh, shut up, Kelly!

18:23.940 --> 18:25.341
Make me, Bob!

18:25.409 --> 18:27.843
Okay, let's take
a ten-minute break!

18:27.911 --> 18:29.545
Oh, God.

18:29.613 --> 18:32.615
This time capsule's
tearing this town apart.

18:32.682 --> 18:33.749
You're leaving soon.

18:33.817 --> 18:35.251
Can I blame it on you
in the press?

18:35.318 --> 18:37.953
Sure.

18:38.021 --> 18:39.822
Well, I got to say,
I think it's kind of impressive.

18:39.890 --> 18:41.123
I've been to a lot of towns.

18:41.191 --> 18:42.858
Usually people don't care
about anything.

18:42.926 --> 18:44.393
I mean, don't get me wrong.

18:44.461 --> 18:46.195
These people are weirdos,

18:46.263 --> 18:50.032
but they're weirdos who care.

18:52.102 --> 18:53.769
Excuse me, everyone.

18:53.837 --> 18:56.872
I realize things have gotten
a little out of control,

18:56.940 --> 18:58.874
and that's Ben's fault,
and he's sorry.

18:58.942 --> 19:00.709
But I have an idea,
and if you like it,

19:00.777 --> 19:03.646
I think we can end this
right now.

19:03.713 --> 19:05.448
"Dear Pawnee of the future,

19:05.515 --> 19:07.283
"congratulations.

19:07.350 --> 19:09.185
"You have found a time capsule

19:09.252 --> 19:11.220
"that was buried
over 50 years ago.

19:11.288 --> 19:14.123
"We wanted to include
a collection of items

19:14.191 --> 19:15.357
"that would best represent

19:15.425 --> 19:18.027
"what life was like in our town
at that moment.

19:18.094 --> 19:20.830
"Instead, you'll find
only one item...

19:20.897 --> 19:24.533
"a video recording
of a public forum we held

19:24.601 --> 19:27.770
"in order to determine
just what those items would be.

19:27.838 --> 19:29.939
"This is truly
what life was like...

19:30.006 --> 19:32.875
"a lot of people
with a lot of opinions

19:32.943 --> 19:34.944
"arguing passionately
for what they believed in.

19:35.011 --> 19:38.047
"So enjoy watching it.

19:38.114 --> 19:40.783
"A-assuming you still have
electricity.

19:40.851 --> 19:43.853
"And sorry about the weird
blank gap in the middle.

19:43.920 --> 19:45.354
"A man named Jerry Gergich

19:45.422 --> 19:47.890
"screwed up
the recording somehow.

19:47.958 --> 19:50.092
"He had one job to do.

19:50.160 --> 19:53.596
Sincerely,
Pawnee of the past."

